Cell C has appointed Nihmal Marrie as Chief Digital Officer of the company. “The telecommunications industry must adapt to the digital world or risk being left behind,” said Cell C CEO Jose Dos Santos. “Nihmal has been tasked with ensuring that Cell C makes the right moves in the digital world, where more of our customers now spend a large part of their lives.” Marrie takes up his new position on 1 August. Marrie joins Cell C from the Liberty Group, where he served as the divisional director for digital and customer value proposition. Before joining Liberty, Marrie was head of business development for Old Mutual Mass Market. He has also co-run his own consultancy, Surya Consulting. Marrie holds a Bachelor of Business Science from the University of Cape Town, with Honours in Finance and Accounting.